    <header>
        <h1><marquee behavior="alternate";bgcolor="yellow";height="1000" >Egg Malai Curry</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>6 hard-boiled eggs, peeled and halved</li>
            <li>1 cup onion, finely chopped</li>
            <li>1 cup tomato, pureed</li>
            <li>1/2 cup cashew nuts, soaked in water</li>
            <li>1/2 cup yogurt</li>
            <li>1/4 cup cream</li>
            <li>1/4 cup ghee or vegetable oil</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon garam masala</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon turmeric powder</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon red chili powder</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon coriander powder</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon cardamom powder</li>
            <li>Salt, to taste</li>
            <li>Fresh cilantro for garnish</li>
            <li>Cooked rice or naan for serving</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a blender, make a smooth paste using soaked cashew nuts and yogurt. Set aside.</li>
            <li>Heat ghee or vegetable oil in a pan over medium heat. Add chopped onions and sauté until golden brown.</li>
            <li>Add ginger-garlic paste and sauté for 1-2 minutes until the raw smell disappears.</li>
            <li>Stir in the tomato puree and cook until the oil starts to separate from the mixture.</li>
            <li>Add garam masala, turmeric powder, red chili powder, coriander powder, and cardamom powder. Mix well.</li>
            <li>Pour in the cashew-yogurt paste and cream. Cook for a few minutes until the masala thickens.</li>
            <li>Place the hard-boiled egg halves into the curry, ensuring they are well coated. Simmer for 5-7 minutes.</li>
            <li>Adjust salt and spice levels according to your taste.</li>
            <li>Garnish with fresh cilantro and serve the Gg Malai Curry hot with rice or naan.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your rich and creamy Gg Malai Curry!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

